Package: shinyStep
Type: Package
Title: Interactive Step Debugger for R Functions in Shiny Apps
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Han", "Zhang", email = "zhangh.ustc@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Embeds an interactive step debugger in a Shiny application.
    Two module types are provided: solo editors for testing a function in
    isolation (Test button, argument test values), and embedded editors for
    debugging a function called from a larger host program (Debug checkbox,
    run_program()). Both support expression-by-expression stepping through
    for/while/repeat/if-else blocks at any nesting depth, live in-frame
    console evaluation, and a green-arrow line highlight in the Ace editor.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: false
Imports:
    shiny (>= 1.7.0),
    shinyAce (>= 0.4.0)
